            "id": "61fce35b03bc461395106",
            "questionText": "A doctor is using a Doppler ultrasound to measure blood flow in an artery. The ultrasound probe emits a sound wave with a frequency of $!$7.5 \\text{ MHz}$!$. The speed of sound in the body is approximately $!$1540 \\text{ m/s}$!$. If the doctor observes a reflected frequency of $!$7.502 \\text{ MHz}$!$, and assuming the blood is flowing towards the probe, calculate the speed of the blood flow in $!$\\text{m/s}$!$. You can assume that the artery is stationary.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "fa7fe16b12404b7aaedcf",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by finding the frequency shift ($!$\\Delta f$!$) by comparing the emitted frequency and the observed frequency. Compute $!$\\Delta f = f' - f_0$!$, where $!$f_0$!$ is the emitted frequency and $!$f'$!$ is the reflected frequency.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "2000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Hz",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "3da3b75d-d472-4d0f-b6e4-c5167dd2fd26",
                        "f09a3cf7-42e1-4878-b989-bb756bfc1f03"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "cf36729ec6ec4f3ba9890",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have calculated the frequency shift, identify the correct formula that relates the frequency shift to the blood flow speed.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27",
                        "bbf4917b-1be4-4827-b1ae-ddfdaa7124a9"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta f = \\frac{2 f_0 v}{c}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta f = \\frac{f_0 v}{c}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta f = \\frac{2 c}{f_0 v}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fbc787f7af19417bb4d12",
                    "stepText": "Now, rearrange the formula to solve for the blood flow speed $!$v$!$. Identify the correct rearranged expression which shows $!$v$!$ in terms of $!$\\Delta f$!$, $!$c$!$, and $!$f_0$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27",
                        "bbf4917b-1be4-4827-b1ae-ddfdaa7124a9"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{\\Delta f\\, c}{2 f_0}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{2 f_0}{\\Delta f\\, c}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{\\Delta f}{2 f_0\\, c}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "70aee7c8b32f4d14b3e4e",
                    "stepText": "Now that you have the rearranged formula, substitute the known values ($!$\\Delta f = 2000 \\text{ Hz}$!$, $!$c = 1540 \\text{ m/s}$!$, and $!$f_0 = 7.5 \\times 10^6 \\text{ Hz}$!$) into the expression $!$v = \\frac{\\Delta f\\, c}{2 f_0}$!$ to compute the blood flow speed.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.2053"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27",
                        "bbf4917b-1be4-4827-b1ae-ddfdaa7124a9"
                    ],
